 Vol. 1: Rare & Previously Unreleased '91-'96]]''\n*Released: October 24, 2004\n*Label: Megatronic (5001)\n*Format: CD\n|}\n\n== Extended plays ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Album details\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''A Private Little War''\n*Released: 1993\n*Label: \n*Format: CS\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[True Force]]''\n*Released: March 25, 1994\n*Label: Curve of the Earth (16)\n*Format: CD\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Korea Tour EP]]''\n*Released: 2005\n*Label: Megatronic\n*Format: CD\n|}\n\n== Singles ==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Title\n!colspan=\"2\"|Peak chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Album\n|-\n!style=\"width:3em;font-size:75%\"| [[Alternative Songs|US<br>Alt.]]<br /><ref name=\"Alternative Songs\">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=powerman 5000|chart=Alternative Songs}}|title=Powerman 5000 Album & Song Chart History: Alternative Songs|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=2009-10-18}}</ref>\n!style=\"width:3em;font-size:75%\"| [[Hot Mainstream Rock Tracks|US<br>Main.]]<br /><ref name=\"Allmusic singles\">{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p200678/charts-awards/billboard-singles|pure_url=yes}}|title=Powerman 5000 > Charts & Awards > ''Billboard'' Singles|work=Allmusic|publisher=Rovi Corporation|accessdate=2011-01-12}}</ref>\n|-\n|1997\n|  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|\"Tokyo Vigilante #1\"\n|  style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align:top;\"|\u2014\n|  style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align:top;\"|\u2014\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''Mega!! Kung Fu Radio''\n|-\n|1998\n|  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|\"Organizized\"\n|  style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align:top;\"|\u2014\n|  style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align:top;\"|\u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1999\n|  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|\"[[When Worlds Collide (Powerman 5000 song)|When Worlds Collide]]\"\n|  style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align:top;\"|18\n|  style=\"text-align:center; vertical-align: