{"title_page": "Denis Lemeunier", "text_new": "{{short description|French wheelchair racer}}\n\n'''Denis Lemeunier''' (born 12 February 1965)<ref>{{cite web |title=Athlete Biography: Lemeunier, Denis |publisher=[[The Beijing Organizing Committee for the Games of the XXIX Olympiad]] |year=2008 |url=http://results.beijing2008.cn/WRMP/ENG/BIO/Athlete/8/1209548.shtml |accessdate=2009-05-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090309142209/http://results.beijing2008.cn/WRMP/ENG/BIO/Athlete/8/1209548.shtml |archive-date=2009-03-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref> is a [[France|French]] wheelchair racer. He is best known for defeating defending champion [[Kevin Papworth]] in the 2001 [[London Marathon]] wheelchair race, a feat given that his wheelchair, which normally would take a year to break in, was only 5 weeks old.<ref>{{cite web | title = London Marathon History | publisher = Flora London Marathon | url = http://www.london-marathon.co.uk/site/content/file/downloads/med_09/4.pdf | format = pdf | accessdate = 2009-05-16 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090424095757/http://www.london-marathon.co.uk/site/content/file/downloads/med_09/4.pdf | archivedate = 2009-04-24 }}</ref> He competed in the [[2004 Summer Paralympics|2004]] and [[2008 Summer Paralympics]], taking a bronze medal in the 4\u00d7400 metre relay the latter year.<ref>{{IPC profile|surname=Lemeunier|givenname=denis}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IPC athlete|id=denis-lemeunier|old_id=868934}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lemeunier, Denis}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male wheelchair racers]]\n[[Category:Paralympic athletes of France]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2004 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic wheelchair racers]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n{{France-Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French wheelchair racer}}\n'''Denis Lemeunier''' (born 12 February 1965)<ref>{{cite web |title=Athlete Biography: Lemeunier, Denis |publisher=[[The Beijing Organizing Committee for the Games of the XXIX Olympiad]] |year=2008 |url=http://results.beijing2008.cn/WRMP/ENG/BIO/Athlete/8/1209548.shtml |accessdate=2009-05-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090309142209/http://results.beijing2008.cn/WRMP/ENG/BIO/Athlete/8/1209548.shtml |archive-date=2009-03-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref> is a [[France|French]] wheelchair racer. He is best known for defeating defending champion [[Kevin Papworth]] in the 2001 [[London Marathon]] wheelchair race, a feat given that his wheelchair, which normally would take a year to break in, was only 5 weeks old.<ref>{{cite web | title = London Marathon History | publisher = Flora London Marathon | url = http://www.london-marathon.co.uk/site/content/file/downloads/med_09/4.pdf | format = pdf | accessdate = 2009-05-16 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090424095757/http://www.london-marathon.co.uk/site/content/file/downloads/med_09/4.pdf | archivedate = 2009-04-24 }}</ref> He competed in the [[2004 Summer Paralympics|2004]] and [[2008 Summer Paralympics]], taking a bronze medal in the 4\u00d7400 metre relay the latter year.<ref>{{IPC profile|surname=Lemeunier|givenname=denis}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IPC athlete|868934}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lemeunier, Denis}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male wheelchair racers]]\n[[Category:Paralympic athletes of France]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2004 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic wheelchair racers]]\n\n\n{{France-athletics-bio-stub}}\n{{France-Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "update IPC external link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denis_Lemeunier"}
